{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.33",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 33,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 33",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 33 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:1",
      "text": "“But now, hear my speech, O Job, and listen to all my words.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:2",
      "text": "Behold, I open my mouth; the tongue in my mouth speaks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:3",
      "text": "My words declare the uprightness of my heart, and what my lips know they speak sincerely.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:4",
      "text": "The spirit of God has made me, and the breath of the Almighty gives me life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:5",
      "text": "Answer me, if you can; set your words in order before me; take your stand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:6",
      "text": "Behold, I am toward God as you are; I too was formed from a piece of clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:7",
      "text": "Behold, no fear of me need terrify you; my pressure will not be heavy upon you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:8",
      "text": "“Surely, you have spoken in my hearing, and I have heard the sound of your words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:9",
      "text": "You say, ‘I am clean, without transgression; I am pure, and there is no iniquity in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:10",
      "text": "Behold, he finds occasions against me, he counts me as his enemy;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:11",
      "text": "he puts my feet in the stocks, and watches all my paths.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:12",
      "text": "“Behold, in this you are not right. I will answer you. God is greater than man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:13",
      "text": "Why do you contend against him, saying, ‘He will answer none of my words’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:14",
      "text": "For God speaks in one way, and in two, though man does not perceive it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:15",
      "text": "In a dream, in a vision of the night, when deep sleep falls upon men, while they slumber on their beds,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:16",
      "text": "then he opens the ears of men, and terrifies them with warnings,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:17",
      "text": "that he may turn man aside from his deed, and cut off pride from man;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:18",
      "text": "he keeps back his soul from the Pit, his life from perishing by the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:19",
      "text": "“Man is also chastened with pain upon his bed, and with continual strife in his bones;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:20",
      "text": "so that his life loathes bread, and his appetite dainty food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:21",
      "text": "His flesh is so wasted away that it cannot be seen; and his bones which were not seen stick out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:22",
      "text": "His soul draws near the Pit, and his life to those who bring death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:23",
      "text": "If there be for him an angel, a mediator, one of the thousand, to declare to man what is right for him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:24",
      "text": "and he is gracious to him, and says, ‘Deliver him from going down into the Pit, I have found a ransom;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:25",
      "text": "let his flesh become fresh with youth; let him return to the days of his youthful vigor’;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:26",
      "text": "then man prays to God, and he accepts him, he comes into his presence with joy. He recounts to men his salvation,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:27",
      "text": "and he sings before men, and says: ‘I sinned, and perverted what was right, and it was not requited to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:28",
      "text": "He has redeemed my soul from going down into the Pit, and my life shall see the light.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:29",
      "text": "“Behold, God does all these things, twice, three times, with a man,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:30",
      "text": "to bring back his soul from the Pit, that he may see the light of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:31",
      "text": "Give heed, O Job, listen to me; be silent, and I will speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:32",
      "text": "If you have anything to say, answer me; speak, for I desire to justify you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.33.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:33",
      "text": "If not, listen to me; be silent, and I will teach you wisdom.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
